@startuml Roles_Permissions_Backoffice_Diagram
title Roles & Permissions Management\nUse Case Diagram - Backoffice Application

left to right direction
skinparam actorStyle awesome

actor "Super Admin" as SA
actor "Backoffice Admin" as BA

SA --|> BA : <<extends>>

rectangle "Backoffice - Roles & Permissions" {
    usecase "View backoffice roles" as UC1
    usecase "View just_causes roles" as UC2
    usecase "Toggle permission on/off (draft)" as UC3
    usecase "Save permission changes" as UC4
    usecase "Discard permission changes" as UC5
    usecase "Create new role" as UC6
    usecase "Deactivate role" as UC7
    usecase "View role assignments" as UC8
    usecase "Filter assignments by role" as UC9
    usecase "Transfer Super Admin" as UC10
}

BA --> UC1
BA --> UC2
BA --> UC3
BA --> UC4
BA --> UC5
BA --> UC6
BA --> UC7
BA --> UC8
BA --> UC9
SA --> UC10

note right of UC3
  Super Admin role card is visible but
  non-interactive: header click is disabled
  and the permissions body never renders.
  Default role is filtered from the list entirely
  and does not appear on this page.
end note

note right of UC10
  3-step confirmation modal requiring
  the new Super Admin's e-mail to be typed.
  Current actor is logged out on success.
end note

@enduml
